{"body": "Printer-friendly version", "citation_label": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals 1", "citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals/block-1", "document_class": "manual", "expression_date": "2026-07-13", "heading": "A-1210, General Policy", "id": "e2b27654-7246-5935-81c8-8550c21a559b", "jurisdiction": "us-tx", "kind": "block", "language": "en", "level": 2, "metadata": {"block_count": 20, "content_type": null, "download_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "fetched_at": "2026-07-13T23:11:39Z", "kind": "block", "recovery_parser": "documents:auto", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "title": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals"}, "ordinal": 1, "parent_citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "parent_id": "0162b845-f0d3-559d-b437-fb175e7240d0", "source_as_of": "2026-07-13", "source_format": "html", "source_id": "release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_path": "sources/us-tx/manual/2026-07-13-recovery/official-documents/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "version": "2026-07-13-recovery"}
{"body": "Revision 24-2; Effective April 1, 2024", "citation_label": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals 2", "citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals/block-2", "document_class": "manual", "expression_date": "2026-07-13", "heading": "Body", "id": "445aa700-018d-564b-8c0c-9f9a267bc5dd", "jurisdiction": "us-tx", "kind": "block", "language": "en", "level": 2, "metadata": {"block_count": 20, "content_type": null, "download_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "fetched_at": "2026-07-13T23:11:39Z", "kind": "block", "recovery_parser": "documents:auto", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "title": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals"}, "ordinal": 2, "parent_citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "parent_id": "0162b845-f0d3-559d-b437-fb175e7240d0", "source_as_of": "2026-07-13", "source_format": "html", "source_id": "release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_path": "sources/us-tx/manual/2026-07-13-recovery/official-documents/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "version": "2026-07-13-recovery"}
{"body": "Resources are assets or possessions that are either countable or exempt, depending on the program and Type of Assistance (TOA) . There are liquid and nonliquid resources. Liquid resources are those that are readily available, such as cash, checking or savings accounts, debit accounts, savings certificates, stocks, or bonds. Nonliquid resources are those that cannot be readily converted to cash, including vehicles, buildings, land, or certain other property. Count the equity value of all resources, liquid and nonliquid, unless otherwise specified or listed as exempt. The equity value is the fair market value (FMV) of an item minus all money owed on the item and the cost associated with the item\u2019s sale or transfer.\n\nCount resources of:\n\nan alien's sponsor;\n\ndisqualified people;\n\nstepparents in TANF households;\n\nmembers of the TANF certified group;\n\nmembers of the SNAP EDG ; and\n\nchildren on TP 32 and TP 56 EDGs.\n\nIf payments exempted as resources are kept in a separate account, those payments remain exempt. If the money is placed in an interest-bearing account, the interest must be counted as income in the month received. If the money is combined with money that is countable, exempt the excluded funds for six months from the date the funds are combined. After six months, the total amount of combined funds should be counted as an available resource.\n\nRelated Policy\n\nResources of an Alien\u2019s Sponsor, A-1245 Resources of Stepparents, A-1247", "citation_label": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals 3", "citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals/block-3", "document_class": "manual", "expression_date": "2026-07-13", "heading": "TANF, SNAP, Children on TP 32 and Children on TP 56", "id": "40f63634-f95d-5c27-8be6-bb84c40cb295", "jurisdiction": "us-tx", "kind": "block", "language": "en", "level": 2, "metadata": {"block_count": 20, "content_type": null, "download_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "fetched_at": "2026-07-13T23:11:39Z", "kind": "block", "recovery_parser": "documents:auto", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "title": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals"}, "ordinal": 3, "parent_citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "parent_id": "0162b845-f0d3-559d-b437-fb175e7240d0", "source_as_of": "2026-07-13", "source_format": "html", "source_id": "release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_path": "sources/us-tx/manual/2026-07-13-recovery/official-documents/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "version": "2026-07-13-recovery"}
{"body": "Categorical eligibility extends to any household authorized to receive services funded by the TANF program. The TANF non-cash (TANF-NC) program offers various services such as family planning, adult education, prevention and treatment of substance abuse, and employment services. Households must pass an income and resource test for determination of categorical eligibility based on receipt of TANF-NC services.\n\nTo meet the resource test, the household\u2019s countable liquid resources plus excess vehicle value must be $5,000 or less. The excess vehicle value can be:\n\nUp to $22,500, of the FMV for the highest valued countable vehicle is exempt. The excess over $22,500 FMV is counted toward the combined resource limit.\n\nUp to $8,700 FMV for all other countable vehicles is exempt. The excess over $8,700 FMV is counted toward the combined resource limit. Note: Refer to vehicle policy for more reasons a vehicle can be exempted.\n\nOnce the recipient is authorized for TANF-NC services based on the initial resource test, all other nonliquid resources are exempt. Regular TANF policy must be followed when determining countable liquid resources within TANF-NC. Most resources are not applicable to SNAP.", "citation_label": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals 4", "citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals/block-4", "document_class": "manual", "expression_date": "2026-07-13", "heading": "SNAP", "id": "a2453e9a-982e-571f-8528-1c5b78b5e573", "jurisdiction": "us-tx", "kind": "block", "language": "en", "level": 2, "metadata": {"block_count": 20, "content_type": null, "download_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "fetched_at": "2026-07-13T23:11:39Z", "kind": "block", "recovery_parser": "documents:auto", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "title": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals"}, "ordinal": 4, "parent_citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "parent_id": "0162b845-f0d3-559d-b437-fb175e7240d0", "source_as_of": "2026-07-13", "source_format": "html", "source_id": "release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_path": "sources/us-tx/manual/2026-07-13-recovery/official-documents/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "version": "2026-07-13-recovery"}
{"body": "Limits, A-1220 Prepaid Burial Insurance, A-1233.2 Vehicles, A-1238 How to Determine Fair Market Value of Vehicles, A-1238.5 General Policy, A-1310 Categorically Eligible Households, B-470 What to Report, B-621", "citation_label": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals 5", "citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals/block-5", "document_class": "manual", "expression_date": "2026-07-13", "heading": "Related Policy", "id": "d4108d11-c28a-55e9-8e46-c73d97036e85", "jurisdiction": "us-tx", "kind": "block", "language": "en", "level": 2, "metadata": {"block_count": 20, "content_type": null, "download_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "fetched_at": "2026-07-13T23:11:39Z", "kind": "block", "recovery_parser": "documents:auto", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "title": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals"}, "ordinal": 5, "parent_citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "parent_id": "0162b845-f0d3-559d-b437-fb175e7240d0", "source_as_of": "2026-07-13", "source_format": "html", "source_id": "release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_path": "sources/us-tx/manual/2026-07-13-recovery/official-documents/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "version": "2026-07-13-recovery"}
{"body": "Resources are not considered a factor in determining eligibility.", "citation_label": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals 6", "citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals/block-6", "document_class": "manual", "expression_date": "2026-07-13", "heading": "Medical Programs Except Children on TP 56 and Children on TP 32", "id": "c33b9670-f72c-5292-bb0e-e46e587f954e", "jurisdiction": "us-tx", "kind": "block", "language": "en", "level": 2, "metadata": {"block_count": 20, "content_type": null, "download_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "fetched_at": "2026-07-13T23:11:39Z", "kind": "block", "recovery_parser": "documents:auto", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "title": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals"}, "ordinal": 6, "parent_citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "parent_id": "0162b845-f0d3-559d-b437-fb175e7240d0", "source_as_of": "2026-07-13", "source_format": "html", "source_id": "release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_path": "sources/us-tx/manual/2026-07-13-recovery/official-documents/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "version": "2026-07-13-recovery"}
{"body": "Resources are considered as a factor in determining eligibility for children on TP 56 and TP 32.\n\nException : Do not consider resources when determining a newborn\u2019s eligibility for TP 56 when the newborn\u2019s mother was eligible for TP 56 or TP 32 at the time of the newborn\u2019s birth.", "citation_label": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals 7", "citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals/block-7", "document_class": "manual", "expression_date": "2026-07-13", "heading": "Children on TP 56 and Children on TP 32", "id": "0c522622-c04b-5022-b17f-a49bcf773b67", "jurisdiction": "us-tx", "kind": "block", "language": "en", "level": 2, "metadata": {"block_count": 20, "content_type": null, "download_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "fetched_at": "2026-07-13T23:11:39Z", "kind": "block", "recovery_parser": "documents:auto", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "title": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals"}, "ordinal": 7, "parent_citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "parent_id": "0162b845-f0d3-559d-b437-fb175e7240d0", "source_as_of": "2026-07-13", "source_format": "html", "source_id": "release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_path": "sources/us-tx/manual/2026-07-13-recovery/official-documents/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "version": "2026-07-13-recovery"}
{"body": "Revision 15-4; Effective October 1, 2015", "citation_label": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals 8", "citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals/block-8", "document_class": "manual", "expression_date": "2026-07-13", "heading": "A\u20141211 Requirement to Pursue Resources", "id": "e5a5a42c-e850-5fe2-b386-06bd37f96f05", "jurisdiction": "us-tx", "kind": "block", "language": "en", "level": 2, "metadata": {"block_count": 20, "content_type": null, "download_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "fetched_at": "2026-07-13T23:11:39Z", "kind": "block", "recovery_parser": "documents:auto", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "title": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals"}, "ordinal": 8, "parent_citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "parent_id": "0162b845-f0d3-559d-b437-fb175e7240d0", "source_as_of": "2026-07-13", "source_format": "html", "source_id": "release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_path": "sources/us-tx/manual/2026-07-13-recovery/official-documents/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "version": "2026-07-13-recovery"}
{"body": "An individual must pursue all resources to which the individual is legally entitled unless it is unreasonable to pursue the resource. Advisors should develop a plan with the individual to pursue the potential resource and allow reasonable time (at least three months) to pursue the resource.\n\nAdvisors should use the comment section of Form TF0001, Notice of Case Action, to inform the individual of the requirement to pursue the resource, including the time the individual has to pursue it, and the resource is not considered available during that time.\n\nIf the individual does not pursue the resource within a reasonable time, the Eligibility Determination Group (EDG) is denied.\n\nException: The individual does not have to pursue a resource if it would be unreasonable. It is unreasonable to pursue a resource if any of the following conditions exist:\n\nThe cost to the individual to pursue the resource exceeds the potential resource's value or causes the individual financial hardship;\n\nPursuing the resource would endanger the individual's health or safety; or\n\nLegal action is required, but a private attorney or legal service refuses to accept the case. The individual must make a reasonable effort to obtain legal assistance.", "citation_label": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals 9", "citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals/block-9", "document_class": "manual", "expression_date": "2026-07-13", "heading": "TANF", "id": "f767118b-e4d6-5373-a2c9-eb045346621c", "jurisdiction": "us-tx", "kind": "block", "language": "en", "level": 2, "metadata": {"block_count": 20, "content_type": null, "download_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "fetched_at": "2026-07-13T23:11:39Z", "kind": "block", "recovery_parser": "documents:auto", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "title": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals"}, "ordinal": 9, "parent_citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "parent_id": "0162b845-f0d3-559d-b437-fb175e7240d0", "source_as_of": "2026-07-13", "source_format": "html", "source_id": "release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_path": "sources/us-tx/manual/2026-07-13-recovery/official-documents/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "version": "2026-07-13-recovery"}
{"body": "Individuals receiving SNAP benefits do not have to pursue resources.\n\nNote: Pursuing resources could help an individual become self-sufficient, and individuals should be provided examples of resources they might be entitled to receive.", "citation_label": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals 10", "citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals/block-10", "document_class": "manual", "expression_date": "2026-07-13", "heading": "SNAP", "id": "9af553c8-0a22-5750-8287-13dadd109fd1", "jurisdiction": "us-tx", "kind": "block", "language": "en", "level": 2, "metadata": {"block_count": 20, "content_type": null, "download_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "fetched_at": "2026-07-13T23:11:39Z", "kind": "block", "recovery_parser": "documents:auto", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "title": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals"}, "ordinal": 10, "parent_citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "parent_id": "0162b845-f0d3-559d-b437-fb175e7240d0", "source_as_of": "2026-07-13", "source_format": "html", "source_id": "release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_path": "sources/us-tx/manual/2026-07-13-recovery/official-documents/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "version": "2026-07-13-recovery"}
