{"body": "In determining an individual's intent for transferring resources for TANF and SNAP benefits, staff must consider the following:\n\nHow recent was the transfer of property? A recent transfer may indicate the household transferred the resource to qualify for benefits.\n\nHow did the applicant support the household after transferring the resource? If the applicant was self-supporting or supported by the person who received the property, then the applicant's intent was to have support rather than qualify for benefits.\n\nHow did the applicant transfer the property? If the applicant loaned the property but cannot recover its value after making a reasonable effort, the applicant is eligible.\n\nSpecial or unpredictable hardships that prevent the individual from making payments for the transferred resource do not affect eligibility. The supervisor and program manager must approve these situations.", "citation_label": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals 16", "citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals/block-16", "document_class": "manual", "expression_date": "2026-07-13", "heading": "TANF and SNAP", "id": "7745e489-55d4-5327-af30-361e16722ff3", "jurisdiction": "us-tx", "kind": "block", "language": "en", "level": 2, "metadata": {"block_count": 20, "content_type": null, "download_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "fetched_at": "2026-07-13T23:11:39Z", "kind": "block", "recovery_parser": "documents:auto", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "title": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals"}, "ordinal": 16, "parent_citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "parent_id": "0162b845-f0d3-559d-b437-fb175e7240d0", "source_as_of": "2026-07-13", "source_format": "html", "source_id": "release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_path": "sources/us-tx/manual/2026-07-13-recovery/official-documents/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "version": "2026-07-13-recovery"}
{"body": "Revision 24-2; Effective April 1, 2024", "citation_label": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals 17", "citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals/block-17", "document_class": "manual", "expression_date": "2026-07-13", "heading": "A\u20141212.3 Length of Denial Period", "id": "5771ccad-bb04-50c4-93ad-d2c2bc31d28d", "jurisdiction": "us-tx", "kind": "block", "language": "en", "level": 2, "metadata": {"block_count": 20, "content_type": null, "download_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "fetched_at": "2026-07-13T23:11:39Z", "kind": "block", "recovery_parser": "documents:auto", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "title": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals"}, "ordinal": 17, "parent_citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "parent_id": "0162b845-f0d3-559d-b437-fb175e7240d0", "source_as_of": "2026-07-13", "source_format": "html", "source_id": "release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_path": "sources/us-tx/manual/2026-07-13-recovery/official-documents/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "version": "2026-07-13-recovery"}
{"body": "Base the length of denial on the amount of the transferred resources that exceed the resource maximum when added to other countable resources.\n\nAmount in Excess of Resource Limit Denial Period $.01 to $249.99 1 month $250 to $999.99 3 months $1,000 to $2,999.99 6 months $3,000 to $4,999.99 9 months $5,000 and more 12 months\n\nExamples:\n\nTANF: A two-person household has $1,250 in a bank account and transfers ownership of a car worth $5,650. Exempt the first $4,650 of the vehicle\u2019s FMV and add the remaining $1,000 to the$1,250 bank account. Subtract the $1,000 resource limit from the total. Use $1,250 to determine the number of months of ineligibility. The household is ineligible for six months.\n\nSNAP: A two-person household has $2,000 in a bank account and transfers ownership of a car worth $26,500. Exempt the first $22,500 of the vehicle\u2019s FMV and add the remaining $4,000 to the $2,000 bank account. Subtract the $5,000 resource limit from the total. Use $1,000 to determine the number of months of ineligibility. The household is ineligible for six months.", "citation_label": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals 18", "citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals/block-18", "document_class": "manual", "expression_date": "2026-07-13", "heading": "TANF and SNAP", "id": "5d66e6c9-5e66-5697-b2ac-f8b00856e7c6", "jurisdiction": "us-tx", "kind": "block", "language": "en", "level": 2, "metadata": {"block_count": 20, "content_type": null, "download_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "fetched_at": "2026-07-13T23:11:39Z", "kind": "block", "recovery_parser": "documents:auto", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "title": "release scope us tx manual 2026 05 27 tx manuals"}, "ordinal": 18, "parent_citation_path": "us-tx/manual/recovery/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "parent_id": "0162b845-f0d3-559d-b437-fb175e7240d0", "source_as_of": "2026-07-13", "source_format": "html", "source_id": "release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_path": "sources/us-tx/manual/2026-07-13-recovery/official-documents/release-scope-us-tx-manual-2026-05-27-tx-manuals", "source_url": "https://www.hhs.texas.gov/handbooks/texas-works-handbook/a-1210-general-policy", "version": "2026-07-13-recovery"}
